1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,640
Your components need to show different things depending on conditions.

2
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:10,520
React handles this with plain Java script.

3
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:16,920
Start with if statements, a function component can return different JSX based on a prop.

4
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:23,080
IsPact is true, return the item with a checkmark, isPact is false, return it without, two

5
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:25,260
separate return statements.

6
00:00:25,260 --> 00:00:27,180
You can also return null.

7
00:00:27,180 --> 00:00:31,540
If isPact is true, return null, the component renders nothing.

8
00:00:31,540 --> 00:00:33,700
It disappears from the output.

9
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,180
But returning null is rare.

10
00:00:36,180 --> 00:00:41,700
Usually, you conditionally include or exclude the component from the parent instead.

11
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:45,100
For inline conditions, use the ternary operator.

12
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:51,940
IsPact questionmark, name plus checkmark colon name, one expression, two outcomes.

13
00:00:51,940 --> 00:00:57,340
Please keep your JSX compact, but don't nest them, deeply nested ternaries are hard

14
00:00:57,340 --> 00:00:58,340
to read.

15
00:00:58,340 --> 00:01:04,540
There's an even shorter pattern, logical end, isPact ampersand ampersand checkmark.

16
00:01:04,540 --> 00:01:09,460
If isPact is true, render the checkmark, if false, render nothing.

17
00:01:09,460 --> 00:01:11,340
Watch out for a common trap.

18
00:01:11,340 --> 00:01:16,180
If the left side is zero, react renders the number zero, not nothing.

19
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:18,940
Use a Boolean condition, not a number.

20
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:24,420
You can also assign JSX to a variable, let item content equals name.

21
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:31,140
Then if isPact, reassign it to name plus checkmark, return the variable in your JSX.

22
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:34,140
This variable approach is the most flexible.

23
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:39,700
You can mix in any logic if else if switch before your return statement.

24
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:44,540
Let's recap, use if and return for completely different JSX.

25
00:01:44,540 --> 00:01:47,700
Use ternary for inline either or choices.

26
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:51,580
Use logical and for conditionally including an element.

27
00:01:51,580 --> 00:01:54,940
Use variables when the logic gets complex.

28
00:01:54,940 --> 00:02:00,780
All of this is just JavaScript, no special react syntax, that's the point.

29
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:02,380
Next up, rendering lists.

